title: [Social Science] Countries where citizens are high in the personality trait "agreeableness" were more likely to follow COVID-19 rules and restrictions, study of 113,083 individuals across 164 countries finds. Countries high in openness and extraversion were less likely.
[Medicine] As Their Numbers Grow, COVID-19 “Long Haulers” Stump Experts - JAMA, september 23. COVID-19 long haulers discussed in the context of other post-viral syndromes
